HEADWORD: Candle foot
<hw>Candle foot</hw>. <fld>(Photom.)</fld> <def>The illumination
produced by a British standard candle at a distance of one foot; -- used
as a unit of illumination.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

